 study questions, this book will be of interest to any student of American studies and will foster an understanding of the United States of America as an imagined community by analyzing the foundational role of myths in the process of nation building.  afunded by Knowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2016: Backlist Collection  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 4aAmerican History. 4aAmerican Studies. 4aCultural Studies. 4aCulture. 4aHistory. 4aIntroduction. 4aLiterature. 4aMyth. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Popular Culture.2bisacsh  aAmerican History.  aAmerican Studies.  aCultural Studies.  aCulture.  aHistory.  aIntroduction.  aLiterature.  aMyth.2 aKnowledge Unlatched - KU Select 2016: Backlist Collectionefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Complete Package 2014z9783110369526oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literature 2014z9783110370331oZDB-23-DLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript English Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066155208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript: Complete eBook-Package 2014z9783110401226oZDB-23-TGP0 cprintz978383761485540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839414859zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839414859/original  a978-3-11-066155-2 transcript English Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2014  aZDB-23-DLWb2014  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-TGPb2014